Fix Fresh's theme key resolution to include all UI dropdown / menu / tab / status / terminal / settings fields, the editor `after_eof_bg`, and the suggestion popup backgrounds.

Previously `Theme::resolve_theme_key` and `Theme::resolve_theme_key_mut` did not cover a large set of `ui.*` fields that exist in `UiColors`, `ThemeFile` and `From<ThemeFile> for Theme`, nor the `editor.after_eof_bg` field. Because `apply_theme_overrides` walks the user theme via `resolve_theme_key_mut`, any field not listed there was silently dropped: the builtin `dark.json` / `light.json` base always won. Most visibly, dropdown menus rendered as the builtin grey `[50, 50, 50]`, suggestion popups (command palette) fell back to the same grey, and the after-EOF dead space rendered as a derived grey from `dark.json`'s base, regardless of the active theme.

This patch extends both match arms in lock-step with the new fields.

